==========================<br />
<br />
<br />
Hello All!!<br />
<br />
   Sorry for the delay over the holiday weeks. I hope everyone had a good break!<br />
<br />
   It&#39;s a new year and a new con season is one its way. First up is Vegas in just a few months. Already there is a lot of buzz regarding the x-list and the next FAQ update (both due next week). We&#39;ll see what Decipher has in store for us. (=<br />
<br />
   See you all in two weeks!!!<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Card Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>I always thought the site number referred to a single block on all cards except the card &quot;Held&quot; which has a special errata. However playing Online a few days ago it allowed my opponent to pull out their ROTK Site 1 (Dunharrow Plateau) with Hobbit Farmer, who states &quot;Site 1&quot;, which I thought meant only FOTR site 1s. Please tell me whether I am simply wrong or if the game is wrong and there is a bug I should be reporting... Thanks, [KOJI]</b><br />
<br />
You are correct. Hobbit Farmer cannot pull your Kings Block Site 1. You should report that one as a bug. (= <br />
<br />
<b>Hi, <br />
I have one question about the new gandalf&#39;s card &quot;Fool&#39;s Hope&quot;: spot gandalf and discard 2 cards from hand to make the opponent discard all but 2 shadow conditions. What does it mean by ALL? It is all shadow cards?possessions,artefacts,minions stacked on site,all conditions except 2. Free peoples active cards are discarded too or just active shadow cards? Thanks for your answer... [Gandalf82]</b><br />
<br />
Fool&#39;s Hope only affects Shadow conditions. It requires the Shadow player to choose 2 Shadow conditions and to discard the rest of their Shadow conditions.<br />
<br />
<b>OK I have two questions: 1) Can Merry&#39;s sword be used to exert more than one minion? For example, if have 5 rohan companions, can I exert Ulaire Enquea 3 times and Grima twice? 2) Can the shadow player remove more than one threat to return more than one card to hand when they play the Witch King, Morgul King? Thanks a lot [Philip]</b><br />
<br />
1. Yes.<br />
<br />
2. No. The Witch-King, Morgul King is a response action that only triggers once, each time you play the Witch-king. If it had the <b>Response:</b> keyword, you could do it multiple times.<br />
<br />
<b>ok the new Eowyn&#39;s sword,dernhelm&#39;s blade says it can be played anytime a skirmish event can and when it is it wounds the minion skirmishing eowyn, and im wondering for example the Balrog Terror of flame and shadow is on eowyn restless maiden, can i discard her sword and bring it back from the discard pile until i kill the balrog with the wounds that it deals out. so to put it simple can the sword be played from the discard pile.[the Easterling]</b><br />
<br />
Incorrect. Unless otherwise noted, you can only use the gametext of a card that is in play or in your hand to be played. You can not play Eowyn&#39;s Sword, Dernhelm&#39;s Blade from your discard pile, just as you can&#39;t do it from your draw deck. Just because it says you can play it when you can play skirmish events, doesn&#39;t allow you to change <b>how</b> it&#39;s played. Only when...<br />
<br />
<h3>Questions about Game/Tournament Rulings:</h3><br />
<b>Hello, I was just wondering about the text of Aragorn, Wingfoot that says he can wound a minion once for each unbound hobbit. Do Hobbit allies such as Farmer Maggot, Bounder, etc. also count towards the total of unbound hobbits? [Gothrist] </b><br />
<br />
By rules definition, <b>Ring-bound</b> and <b>unbound</b> can only apply to companions, not allies. Merry and Pippin are the only unbound Hobbits and Sam and Frodo are the only Ring bound Hobbits currently in the game.<br />
<br />
<b>The limit of threats is equal to the number of companions. Lets say the number of threats is 5 with 5 companions and a companion is discarded, not killed (common TTT Merry or Pippin or something). What happens? Does the fifth threat &quot;disappear&quot;, or does it stay? Thanks a lot, [KOJI] </b><br />
<br />
The threat limit rule prevents you from <b>adding</b> threats once the total equals (or is greater to) the number of companions currently in play. As you described, it is possible to have more threats than companions, but that is only when enough threats are in play and companions are discarded. Discarding a companion does not affect the threat total. The number of threats doesn&#39;t change and threat wounds are not applied.<br />
<br />
<b>I have another LOTR question for you. When a companion dies the tokens in the threat pool turn into wounds. We all know that, but I am unclear on when this actually happens. For example: I have a Witch King, Deathless Lord going against an exausted companion. The Witch King wins the skirmish and as a result I can exert a companion. Are the threat wounds added before or after the exertion? [Death Dealer]</b><br />
<br />
If the Witch-king, Deathless Lord is in play and a Nazgul kills a companion there are 2 mandatory actions that trigger.<br />
  1. Place the companion in the Deal Pile and threat wounds are placed on companions by the Free People&#39;s Player.<br />
  2. The Witck-king&#39;s game text to wound an ally twice or exert a companion once.<br />
<br />
Whenever there are two or more mandatory actions that result from the same trigger, they are resolved in the order of the FPP&#39;s choosing. So it would be up to the FPP to decide whether or not they want to apply the threat wounds before or after the Witch-king exerts a companion.<br />
<br />
<b>Faramir, wizards pupil can exert gandalf to prevent all wounds to faramir. My question is, what happens if someone is about to die, so as a skirmish action the free peoples player exerts gandalf, and the threat wounds are triggered, can faramir &#39;suck them up&#39;? can you assign them to him, but because he&#39;s superman, they bounce off, never to be seen again? thanks! [Machine]</b><br />
<br />
Cards that prevent wounds are different than cards that limit the amount of wounds a character can receive. The best example is Gimli&#39;s Helm, since it has both functions.<br />
<br />
While wearing his helm, Gimli may only take 1 wound per skirmish phase. Regardless of the source, only 1 wound per skirmish phase may be placed on Gimli. Any wounds over that limit must be placed on a different valid target. So if you were applying 3 threat wounds, only 1 could be placed on Gimli while the rest would have to be placed on other valid companions. If Gimli lost a skirmish to a minion that was Damage +2, only 1 wound would be placed on Gimli. The other 2 wounds that he should have taken would not be placed on anyone, since there is only one valid target for placing wounds for losing a skirmish.<br />
<br />
If as a Skirmish Action, you discard the helm all wounds that were to be placed on Gimli in this skirmish phase would be ignored and have no effect. So in the above examples, you could apply all 3 threat wounds to Gimli, but they would have 0 effect on him. Gimli would also take no wounds for losing a Skirmish to a Damage +2 minion.<br />
<br />
Cards like Gimli&#39;s Helm (Skirmish Action) and Faramir, Wizard&#39;s Pupil are great ways of safely dealing with threat wounds.<br />
<br />
<b>If I use The Board Is Set to cancel Captured by the Ring, is Gollum still played? Is playing Gollum the cost, and adding the threat the event&#39;s result? If I cancel We Wants It, does the Shadow player still pay for Gollum, or is it cancelled before Gollum would have been paid for. Similar issues arise with cards like Host of Thousands. How does Board Set interact with such cards??? If my opponent pays to cancel Boards and then cannot afford Gollum, is the event discarded without effect? Thanks for any clarification you can offer! [HungTroll]</b><br />
<br />
The Board is Set is a Response action to the Shadow player playing an event. The Shadow players has not &quot;played&quot; the event until all requirements are met and all costs are paid. When the Board is Set is player, the effects of the Shadow player&#39;s event are ignored.<br />
<br />
For Captured by the Ring, playing Gollum is a cost of the event. The Shadow player would have to pay the 2 twilight and play Gollum BEFORE you had the opportunity to play The Board is Set. Once you play The Board is Set, Gollum is already in play. The effect of adding a threat is all that is prevented. Since Gollum is already in play when you play The Board is Set, the situation of not having enough twilight to play Gollum is moot.<br />
<br />
<b>You have almost already answered this question but I would like a more clear &quot;rule of thumb&quot; to follow in loop situations. There are several that seem to crop up now, Smeagol (add a burden to go +2)vs minion at site 4 (remove a burden to go +2). This can be HUGE because of some of Smeagols response actions. Hrethel vs a Warg Rider. Gollum vs Knights spear. There needs to be a simple &quot;loop&quot; rule. Can they do it once each? Not at all? Until one dies of boredom? The FP player wins? Thanks a lot. Your rulings are always very helpful.  [Big Yoda]</b><br />
<br />
As always, the players must trust and abide by their Tournament Directors. In unclear situations like these, the TD must make a decision and the players should follow it. My advice is that every TD make a fair decision, stand by it and be consistant throughout the tournament. If a TD rules what the outcome of the skirmish between Gollum and a Knight with Spear and the players continue to add and remove a threat, I would give each a warning for slow play. The players should accept the ruling and move one from there.<br />
<br />
I can&#39;t tell you the result of every time a Knight with Knight&#39;s Spear goes up against Gollum, becuase there will always be different outside factors that affect the outcome. (Such as who needs to add or remove the threat first? Who would win the skirmish if neither player has access to the Skirmish action?) By removing the loop I usually find the answer I need to make the ruling. Once I make my ruling, they players are free to do what the wish, but as I mentioned, to continue the loop would run the risk of receiving a warning.<br />
<br />
<b>Once someone is assigned to a skirmish by an event or a special ability can they later be reassigned by another event or special ability or are they &quot;locked in&quot;? For example Smeagol Always Helps, adds 2 threats to Assign Lurtz to fight him and exhausts him. The shadow player has a bad feeling about this and wants to use Saruman SOTE to send Lutrz to Legolas. Can he?  [Big Yoda]</b><br />
<br />
No. All assignment actions are done on a one versus one basis and may only affect previously unassigned characters. (I&#39;m talking about cards that say &quot;<b>Event Assignment</b>&quot; or &quot;<b>Assignment:</b>&quot;.) Once a character is assigned to a skirmish, they are no longer valid targets for other assignment actions.<br />
<br />
Note: This does not prevent a Defender +X companion from assigning to more than one minion at the &quot;Assign Defenders&quot; part of the phase. It also does not prevent the Shadow player from assigning more than one minion to the same skirmish during the &quot;Assign Leftover Minions&quot; part of the phase.<br />
<br />
<h3>Star Wars:CCG Rulings</h3><br />
<b>As I understand you do star wars rulings. I&#39;m not sure where else to get your d-mail and if I am wrong could you tell me who to talk to? Anyway, my questions: Are AT-ATs considered to be presence by imperials? I control three raltiir sites with AT-ATs with permanent pilots and nothing else. Does my Raltiir ops objective flip? There is no independent symbol on the vehicle cards. Similarly: If I control/occupy systems/sectors with non-independent dark side star ships, is it considered to be controlled/occupied by an imperial? Raltiir ops says my total b-destiny is +X for each raltiir location i occupy with an imperial, if that changes anything. What vehicles can go to cloud sectors? Just combat vehicles? just vehicles with manuever? just combat vehicles with manuever? Let&#39;s say Bespin is blown away. 4 asteroid sectors (3 reg ones and Big One), and 4 cloud sectors (3 reg ones and Bespin: Cloud City). When asteroid destiney is drawn how much is added for asteroid sectors? 4 for the 4 actual ones? 5 because the planet is blown away as well? or 9 because of the 4 cloud sectors related to Bespin? A star ship may only move 2 sectors per turn, right? Or through one sector to the next parsec or to next parsec and then into a sector or whatever the movement is. 2 sectors, right? Is it also 2 sectors for death star 2 sectors? Dagobah rules. What are they? Specifically: Who can deploy to dagobah Are the locations battlegrounds Can ships land at non-docking bay sites, let passengers off, and then take off next turn (assuming the site doesn&#39;t deal with ships in it&#39;s text). Thanks and sorry if you&#39;re not the right guy and I just wasted your time....also sorry about all the questions if you ARE the right guy....and thanks for your time nonetheless  [Alex Maslow]</b><br />
<br />
Yes, I still am happy to answer Star Wars questions if you guys have some. It&#39;s just been a while since anyone asked me one.<br />
<br />
An Imperial is determined by the icon in the upper lefthand corner of the card. It&#39;s the blue circular one. If the card does not have that icon, then it is not an Imperial. So you would not be able to flip Raltiir Ops with only AT-ATs, other combat vehicles, or starships.<br />
<br />
movement – regular – sector movement, clouds<br />
Any piloted starfighter (or cloud car, shuttle vehicle or patrol craft that is piloted<br />
and has a landspeed of greater than zero) may conduct any of the following<br />
moves for 1 Force during the owner&#39;s move phase:<br />
• from the system to the highest-altitude related cloud sector or vice versa.<br />
• from a cloud sector up to two related cloud sectors away per move.<br />
• between the lowest-altitude cloud sector and a related exterior site (see<br />
movement – regular – landing, movement – regular – taking off).<br />
<br />
Blown away systems do not become Asteroid Sectors. If you has 3 Asteroid Fields and Big One at the system, the maximum bonus to the Asteriod Destiny would be 4.<br />
<br />
You may only move 1 Death Star II sector per move.<br />
<br />
Characters, vehicles, starships, weapons, devices and Utinni Effects may not<br />
deploy to Dagobah locations unless:<br />
• the card is specifically allowed to deploy due to the game text on the Dagobah location itself. E.g. Dagobah Bog Clearing.<br />
• the card is specifically permitted to &quot;deploy to Dagobah&quot; or is permitted to deploy &quot;regardless of location deployment restrictions.&quot;<br />
• the weapon or device is deploying on a card already at Dagobah.<br />
<br />
Dagobah locations are never battlegrounds.<br />
<br />
Yes, all starfighters (except TIEs) can land at exterior sites.<br />
<br />
Feel free to write me if ever you have a Star Wars rules question. The official source for Star Wars Rules is rules@swccgpc.com.<br />
<br />
<br />
- Enrique<br />
<br />
